Another EUR 400 million for infrastructure
Minister for Finance János Veres and Marta Gayecka, Vice-President of the European Investment Bank (EIB), signed three credit agreements in Budapest on Friday, with a total value of EUR 400 million, which is intended to cover education, transport and environmental infrastructure and energy.
