The Congress agrees with the MIFID directive, which entered into force on 1 November.
In parallel with the parliamentary preparation, which today ended its meeting with the Congress Decision in the Senate on the requests for additional / amendments to the project, the government published the provisions of the new law, with the aim of allowing the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of the congressmen and senates, who in their negotiations and votes had the aim of establishing the best possible arrangements to ensure the security of investors and to regulate individual business activities in order to ensure a generally efficient market situation.
In addition to the modernisation of financial markets, the MIFID, which redefines the Investment Services Regulation, is pursuing an improvement in investor protection, an increase in the Spanish Investment Commission's (CNMV) control rights and the promotion of cooperation between the various European Union control authorities.
The new Directive allows for the provision of financial advice to both specialised companies and to natural or legal persons, and also contributes to the establishment of new financial services companies (ESIS), to the advisory companies which are combined with the investment and intermediary companies of securities.
It also extends the number of systems for the execution of financial transactions, so that the regulated circulation markets are added to the multilateral systems of the securities business and the systems for the internationalisation of trade orders, which would eventually compete with the current economic operators.
The law requires investment companies to inform the priorities of their business profile, the confrontation and the forms of dealing with risks on the market and to register all projects carried out in order to facilitate the control of the CNMV.
The Congress's Economic Commission subsequently provided for further changes, with the decision that the debt securities issued with titles must now be considered as complex financial resources due to their high risk to the investor, confirmed by the US mortgage and banking crisis. (US mortgage crisis)
In addition, the entry into force of the Directive on the legal limitation of the fields of work of diplolized economists was used; 30 years after the 1977 regulation, which restricted the fields of work reserved for the economists, was adopted.
The Senate, for its part, established new positions in the financial sector, such as those of the economic mediator who works on a foreign account, does not need the authorisation of the CNMV and can offer its services for the commercialisation of products and for the purchase of customers at the same time several investment companies.
The harmonised index of consumer prices (CPI) increased by five-tenths in November and is now 4.1%.
The indicator used by Eurostat to assess the inflation rate within the European Union is the average price trend in Spain in November.
Its publication is in line with the principles of Eurostat and the European Central Bank (ECB), which seek to compare the location and quality of the data with US products by the disclosure of the data.
The forecast for the indicator can be prepared in advance by using the same approach as for the harmonised consumer price index, while using various other statistical modelling methods to estimate the information not available at the time of the calculation.
However, the Spanish Statistical Office (INE) warned that the pre-established indicator was only a benchmark and therefore did not have to be consistent with the final result announced on 14 December.
