Which insurance is best for me?
The motor vehicle insurance scheme, which covers a possible case of damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which once again depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of production of the driving licence, family status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, one must be clear about what we are dealing with here.
A car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurance undertaking.
This agreement shall be recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract which establishes that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to submit the corresponding amount of the settlement in the event of an injury.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance which is composed of several factors, including age, sex, time of production of the driving licence, family status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance undertakings shall set their prices according to the statistics, so that, in the event of a higher risk of accident, higher contribution payments are also due.
For this reason, both over 25 years old and women have to pay less contributions, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, as they, according to the statistical values and therefore also in the company's conviction, tend to be less accidents than single persons.
The benefits of the vehicle are affected by the frequency of the driving and therefore the probability of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
In drawing up the premium, insurance must take into account a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation in detail in order to select the car insurance that is most likely to meet his personal needs.
We are now listing the most important points to be considered in the selection of insurance in order to make not only a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
The under-25-year-olds meet many obstacles in the choice of low-cost insurance, such as low driving practice and the young driving licence.
Even if it was best for an ideal insurance scheme to complete a full-scale insurance scheme, there are still more expensive alternatives.
The careful drivers can select a full-scale casco with self-participation, so that the services of a full-scale insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer has to pay part of the amount of the damage itself.
The amount is fixed before the conclusion of the contract and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher than the amount to be paid, says Luis Noguera, Spain's main representative at First Europe, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is the extended insurance that ensures the customers against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused by the car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25 years old, it is in your hand to reduce the insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate of the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty shall include an increase in the rates in question.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it may allow to increase the bonus payments, explains Noguera.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for the drivers to conclude a contract. This is the reason for the fact that with increasing driving practice the accident rate is falling.
It is therefore most appropriate to opt for full-time insurance with self-participation.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, the Spanish manager of the European company explains, and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been dropped.
However, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take out full-time insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the person concerned allows it.
On the part of the insurers, couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate and therefore their contributions are also low.
In this case, a full-scale insurance with self-participation (with an amount of around 300 euros) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, an extended insurance is recommended, which only takes place for the third year of the vehicle.
They are more relaxed and have a greater purchasing power, which allows them to start a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera notes.
For pensioners, it is appropriate to provide full-time insurance with self-participation (with an amount of around 150 euros), or an extended insurance that only uses in the case of a sufficiently high credit.
In the end, it must be noted that car insurance is a very important thing, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it has high costs that require a thorough selection that is in line with our personal situation.
